---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
import { site, telLink, mailLink } from '../data/site';

const title = 'Cookie Policy | TJ Mods (Proper Mods Ltd) East London';
const description =
  'How TJ Mods (Proper Mods Ltd) uses cookies. We set only essential cookies by default and use optional analytics only with your consent.';
const lastUpdated = '02/06/2026';
---
<Layout title={title} description={description} current="/cookie-policy">
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Cookie Policy"
    subtitle="What cookies are, the small number this website uses, and how you stay in control of them."
    crumb="Cookie Policy"
  />

  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-prose fade-in">
        <p class="mono text-[0.82rem] uppercase tracking-wider text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

        <p>
          This Cookie Policy explains how <strong>{site.legalName}</strong> (trading as <strong>{site.name}</strong>) uses
          cookies and similar technologies on this website. It should be read alongside our
          <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>. By "this website" we mean the pages published at our domain.
        </p>

        <h2>1. What are cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that a website can place on your device when you visit. They are widely used to make
          websites work, to remember your preferences, and to provide information to the site owner. Similar technologies,
          such as your browser's <strong>localStorage</strong>, can store small amounts of data in much the same way.
          Cookies can be "session" cookies (deleted when you close your browser) or "persistent" cookies (which remain for a
          set period).
        </p>

        <h2>2. The cookies this website uses</h2>
        <p>
          We keep cookies to a minimum. By default, this website sets only <strong>essential cookies and local storage</strong>
          that are strictly necessary for the site to function and to remember your cookie choices.
        </p>

        <h3>Essential (always active)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Cookie consent preference</strong> - when you respond to our cookie banner, we store your choice in your
            browser's localStorage so we do not ask you again on every visit. This is set on your own device and is not
            shared with anyone.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Essential storage of this kind does not require your consent under the Privacy and Electronic Communications
          Regulations (PECR), because it is necessary to provide a service you have asked for.
        </p>

        <h3>Analytics (optional - only with your consent)</h3>
        <p>
          We may use privacy-respecting analytics to understand, in aggregate, how visitors use the site so we can improve
          it. Any such analytics cookies are <strong>only set if you give your consent</strong> through our cookie banner.
          If you decline, no analytics cookies are placed.
        </p>

        <h3>Third-party cookies (Google Maps)</h3>
        <p>
          We embed a <strong>Google Maps</strong> map so you can find our studio in {site.address.area}. When this map
          loads, Google may set its own cookies and process limited technical data. These cookies are controlled by Google,
          not by us. You can learn more in
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/cookies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's cookie information</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Managing and disabling cookies</h2>
        <p>
          You are always in control. You can manage cookies in several ways:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>On our cookie banner</strong> - choose whether to accept optional cookies when you first visit.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>In your browser settings</strong> - most browsers let you block or delete cookies and clear stored site
            data. Doing so may affect how some parts of the site work. Help is available for
            <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chrome</a>,
            <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Safari</a>,
            <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-GB/kb/clear-cookies-and-site-data-firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Firefox</a> and
            <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-gb/microsoft-edge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Edge</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Withdrawing your consent</h2>
        <p>
          You can withdraw your consent to optional (analytics) cookies at any time. The simplest way is to clear this
          site's stored data in your browser, which removes your saved preference and lets you make a fresh choice the next
          time you visit. You can also block cookies entirely through your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. Any changes will be published on this page with a revised
          "Last updated" date.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about our use of cookies, please contact <strong>{site.legalName}</strong> at
          {site.address.street}, {site.address.area}, {site.address.city} {site.address.postcode}, by email at
          <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a>, or by phone on <a href={telLink}>{site.phoneDisplay}</a>. For more on how we
          handle personal data, see our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-snow py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="card-feature flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-6 fade-in">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow mb-3">Prefer to ask a person?</span>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-balance">Get in touch</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mt-2 text-pretty">Call us or send an email and we will be glad to help.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 flex-shrink-0">
          <a href={telLink} class="btn btn-primary"><Icon name="Phone" size={16} strokeWidth={2.3} /> {site.phoneDisplay}</a>
          <a href={mailLink} class="btn btn-outline"><Icon name="Mail" size={16} strokeWidth={2.1} /> Email us</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
